   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="letter">
            <pb n="1" facs="Edgeworth_Harvard_604742_1829-12_page01.jpg"/>
            <p>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeM1">Miss Edgeworth</persName>'s compliments<lb/>
                    to <persName ref="./Personography.xml#MackJ1">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. Mackay</persName> - she has been<lb/>
                    intending ever since she<lb/>
                    has been in this <choice>
                  <orig>neighbor<lb/>
                        hood</orig>
                  <reg>neighborhood</reg>
               </choice> to <del>have</del> indulge her<lb/>
                    self in a visit to the Coll<hi rend="superscript">ge</hi>
               <lb/>
                    Botanic garden - But<lb/>
                    weather now and her<lb/>
                    ill health when weather<lb/>
                    permitted have deprived<lb/>
                    her of this pleasure<lb/>
                    She leaves <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Bloomfield_IE">Bloomfield</placeName> early<lb/>
                    on Saturday <choice>
                  <abbr>morn<hi rend="superscript">g</hi>.</abbr>
                  <reg>morning</reg>
               </choice> -<lb/>
                    Her only chance of having<lb/>
                    the pleasure of seeing <persName ref="./Personography.xml#MackJ1">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>.<lb/>
                    Mackay</persName> is his coming to<lb/>
                    see her tomorrow as she will<lb/>
                    be all day at home -<lb/>
                    The family <add>has</add> breakfast late<lb/>
                    &amp; would be happy if<lb/>
               <pb n="2" facs="Edgeworth_Harvard_604742_1829-12_page02.jpg"/>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#MackJ1">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. M</persName> could join them.<lb/>
            </p>
            <p>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeM1">Miss E</persName> wishes to talk to<lb/>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#MackJ1">Mr. Mackay</persName> about some<lb/>
                    American plants <unclear>as</unclear> she<lb/>
                    is going to write to her<lb/>
                    friend, in <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#US">America</placeName> again<lb/>
                    who may <hi rend="underline">do better</hi> with<lb/>
                    some <hi rend="underline">useful</hi>
               <hi rend="underline">hints</hi>
               <lb/>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeM1">Miss E</persName> has also <title ref="./Workography.xml#Conve1">a <add>new</add> book<lb/>
                        of <persName ref="./Personography.xml#MarcJ1">Mrs. Marcet</persName>s on Botany</title>
               <lb/>
                    which she wishes to shew<lb/>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#MackJ1">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. Mackay</persName> &amp; to lend<lb/>
                    to him if he has no other<lb/>
                    means of obtaining it.<lb/>
            </p>
            <p>It contains all <persName ref="./Personography.xml#CandA1">de Candolle</persName>s<lb/>
               <hi rend="underline">new matter</hi>
               <lb/>
            </p>
            <closer>
               <dateline>
                  <date when="1829-12-23">Dec. 23<hi rend="superscript">d</hi> 1829</date>
                  <lb/>
                    Wednesday Eve<hi rend="superscript">g</hi>
               </dateline>
               <lb/>
               <pb n="3" facs="Edgeworth_Harvard_604742_1829-12_page03.jpg"/>
